The paper discusses the implementation and reproduction of results for the Deep Q-Network, which is a popular deep reinforcement learning algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the algorithm for a range of domains, which could be related to cs.RO (Robotics).
